{"name":"Berserker Horde","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 90\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 9th level, carve a <em>rune of the berserker</em>, venture into the savage wilderness, and then stab one&rsquo;s palm with a knife for 1d4 hp damage. Whilst howling like a beast, the runegraver smears the fresh blood on the rune, attracting <strong>50 wild berserkers</strong> of an alignment that roughly corresponds with that of the runegraver. These feral warriors will arrive over the course of 1d4 days. They will follow their runegraver lord until death, so long as their lives comprise violence, bloodshed, drink, and revelry. Providing food and shelter for the horde is the responsibility of the runegraver. Unless the referee permits otherwise, a <em>berserker horde</em> can be summoned but once every five years; furthermore, introducing these wild people to civilization can prove disastrous.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver 9","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679264898731,"modifiedTime":1681579127776,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"8MoRGKYpPNaZ0y7u","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Grave Runes","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 87\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Runegravers grave runes on specific materials that are carved, smoothed, and shaped by the runegraver. Each rune emulates a specific spell, with no other material components required. The number and levels of rune spells cast per day are charted on <strong>Table 49</strong> (<strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 87).</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Runes are enchanted when the runegraver cuts his or her palm (no damage at this time), drips blood on the rune, and then recites the appropriate poem. Much like spells memorized from books, when a rune spell is cast, the rune and its medium remain, but their sorcery is drained until the process is started anew.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Runes are invoked (cast) much like a spell, except each invocation costs the runegraver a sacrifice of 1 hit point per spell level, pain coursing up the runegraver&rsquo;s arms. So, casting a level 3 rune spell entails a loss of 3 hp, which can be recovered in the usual manner. Should the runegraver drop below 1 hp from evoking a rune, unconsciousness is staved off for 1 turn, pending an <em>extraordinary feat of constitution</em>.</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Each of the 16 runes may be invoked but once per day. The runes and the spells they mimic are as follows:</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>Level 1:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>giant</strong>&ndash;<em>enlargement</em></li>\n<li><strong>man</strong>&ndash;<em>command</em></li>\n<li><strong>riding</strong>&ndash;<em>mount</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Level 2:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>constraint</strong>&ndash;<em>hold person</em></li>\n<li><strong>shower</strong>&ndash;<em>black cloud</em></li>\n<li><strong>wealth</strong>&ndash;<em>fool&rsquo;s gold</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Level 3:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>plenty</strong>&ndash;<em>create food and water</em></li>\n<li><strong>ulcer</strong>&ndash;<em>inflict disease</em> (reverse of <em>cure disease</em>)</li>\n<li><strong>yew</strong>&ndash;<em>twofold missile</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Level 4:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>hail</strong>&ndash;<em>ice storm</em> (hail)</li>\n<li><strong>ice</strong>&ndash;<em>freeze surface</em></li>\n<li><strong>Tyr</strong>&ndash;<em>dweomered weapon</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Level 5:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>god</strong>&ndash;<em>true seeing</em></li>\n<li><strong>sun</strong>&ndash;<em>flame strike</em></li>\n<li><strong>water</strong>&ndash;<em>control water</em></li>\n</ul>\n<p>Level 6:</p>\n<ul>\n<li><strong>birch</strong>&ndash;<em>reincarnation</em></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>A runegraver begins with a single rune, a sacred mystery revealed by a master. It is either selected or randomly determined upon character creation (consult your referee). Runegravers unlock the secret of a new rune or runes at each level gain, at the following schedule:</p>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<ul>\n<li>1st level: &times;1 level 1 rune</li>\n<li>2nd level: &times;1 level 1 rune</li>\n<li>3rd level: &times;1 level 1 rune; &times;1 level 2 rune</li>\n<li>4th level: &times;1 level 2 rune</li>\n<li>5th level: &times;1 level 2 rune; &times;1 level 3 rune</li>\n<li>6th level: &times;1 level 3 rune</li>\n<li>7th level: &times;1 level 3 rune; &times;1 level 4 rune</li>\n<li>8th level: &times;1 level 4 rune</li>\n<li>9th level: &times;1 level 4 rune; &times;1 level 5 rune</li>\n<li>10th level: &times;1 level 5 rune</li>\n<li>11th level: &times;1 level 5 rune</li>\n<li>12th level: &times;1 level 6 rune</li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 88\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>New runes are acquired via spiritual revelation, the uncloaking of runic lore, or deific favour from Ullr. Each new rune is learnt automatically, with no need of a qualification roll. Runegravers do not learn new runes outside of level gains, but by 12th level, all 16 runes have been mastered.</p>\n<p>[<strong>Table 50: Runes</strong> -- see <strong>Player's Manual</strong>, p. 88]</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":null,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YIplOKcVwiJ20PGF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579127776,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"Fu1gyOHTUGnMlxyg","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Extraordinary Strength","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 27\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>+8% chance to perform <em>extraordinary feats of strength</em> (see <strong>Chapter 3: Statistics</strong>, <em>strength</em>).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver","roll":"d100","rollType":"below","rollTarget":8,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{"core":{"sourceId":"Item.YIplOKcVwiJ20PGF"}},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679249969686,"modifiedTime":1681579127776,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"O6zsG6POkQyblm0O","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Nithing Pole","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 90\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 7th level, a runegraver can select a strong branch and carve it with all manner of signs, sigils, and execrations in the Old Norse language, amongst them the proper name of an enemy. The <em>nithing pole</em> must be staked into the ground and mounted with the head or skull of a goat, horse, sheep, or like animal. It must face in the direction of the named target&rsquo;s abode, within a quarter mile. The effect is equivalent to a <em>bestow curse</em> spell (see reverse of <em>remove curse</em>), except the duration is permanent until the <em>nithing pole</em> is located and nullified with a <em>remove curse</em> or <em>dispel magic</em> spell. Physically destroying the pole will not lift the curse. A <em>nithing pole</em> can be created once per month.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver 7","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679264898731,"modifiedTime":1681579127777,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"ZBWx5ou9BNPOHl9c","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Ale Horn","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 89\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>An aurochs (or other bovine) drinking horn painstakingly etched in Nordic designs. Once per day, if the horn is filled with 12 ounces of fresh water, the runegraver can turn the water to enchanted ale that restores 2 hp per CA level when drunk. The ale can be shared, but once uncapped, the entire contents must be imbibed within 6 rounds. Once per week, three drops of honey added to the water-filled drinking horn produces magical mead that can <em>cure disease</em> (as the spell).</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679264898731,"modifiedTime":1681579127776,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"bPQvlXGwUJNdhAG5","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
{"name":"Casting of Lots","type":"ability","img":"modules/hyperborea-content/assets/icons/ability.png","system":{"description":"<div class=\"page\" title=\"Page 89\">\n<div class=\"layoutArea\">\n<div class=\"column\">\n<p>At 5th level, a runegraver can gather 16 fresh twigs. The twigs must be smoothed and engraved, each incised with one of the 16 runes listed on <strong>Table 50: Runes</strong>. They are then placed in a leather pouch filled with powdered bone. To <em>cast lots</em>, the runegraver must engage in a 1-turn ritual, chanting, shaking the pouch, and finally dumping the twigs from the pouch. The runegraver then articulates a question, selects three bone dust&ndash;covered twigs, wipes them clean, and interprets their meaning. <em>Casting of lots</em> is otherwise equivalent to an <em>augury</em> spell. It can be performed once per day.</p>\n</div>\n</div>\n</div>","autoTags":[],"manualTags":[],"save":"","pattern":"transparent","requirements":"runegraver 5","roll":"","rollType":"result","rollTarget":0,"blindroll":false,"tags":[]},"effects":[],"flags":{},"_stats":{"systemId":"hyperborea","systemVersion":"1.000","coreVersion":"10.291","createdTime":1679264898731,"modifiedTime":1681579127776,"lastModifiedBy":"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea"},"_id":"bmUiNW4wyVOghtXV","folder":null,"sort":0,"ownership":{"default":0,"Sp6Zt9CdjPzQ3Qea":3}}
